main event: Report of unidentified aircraft tracked at high speed on radar, noted on 2 July 1963.
interesting points: The report mentions 3 high-speed aircraft identified on radar but not classified as UFOs,The aircraft were tracked heading at 250 degrees,The position of the radar tracking was at coordinates 54N 35W,The report involved several military branches including the Air Force, Army, and Navy,There are no photographs associated with this report.
witness description: military personnel involved in the radar tracking
